Both files emitted in the working directory:
- `transcript.json`: 25 iterations, 376 hypotheses, 376 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`.
- `analysis_summary.txt`: narrative walkthrough.

**Headline finding.** Of the six treatments, only `treatment_palbociclib` shows a robust PFS effect, sharply concentrated in the joint subgroup `er_positive=1 AND her2_positive=0 AND pik3ca_mutation=0 AND ki67_pct < 14`, where palbociclib lengthens mean PFS by ~+4.94 months (n_on ≈ 3,829; n_off ≈ 6,923; p < 1e-300). Outside this subgroup the effect is null (+0.016 mo, p = 0.48). Each of the four markers is necessary — leave-one-out and within-complement tests both confirm. Adjusted interaction is +4.97 mo (p < 1e-300) after controlling for 14 prognostic covariates. The Ki67 threshold sits sharply at ~14.

For the other five treatments (tamoxifen, trastuzumab, olaparib, sacituzumab govitecan, pembrolizumab) no biomarker-defined subgroup yields an adjustment-robust PFS benefit; even on-label populations (trastuzumab in HER2+, olaparib in BRCA-mutated TNBC, tamoxifen in ER+) come back null after adjustment.
